@f2404 I don't think "I lost what I was reading in Read-Only mode by an inadvertent keystroke" is similar to "While I'm reading this o/p in Read-Only mode let me scroll above/down a little using Ctrl-Alt-Arrow"

One is a mistake and if I'm not wrong the purpose of "Read-Only" mode is to shield the use from that mistake. And another one is deliberate shortcut used.

As mentioned in the report we can disable 'Scroll on keystroke' when 'Read-Only' is selected. Thereby protecting the user from a keystroke by mistake (serving the purpose of Read-Only mode) and also can use the Ctrl-Alt-Arrow shortcut at the same time.

